			<description><![CDATA[<p>
<br />
<u><strong>Job Description</strong></u></p>
<p>
The Manufacturing Engineering Manager is responsible for all of the manufacturing engineering activities including: lean manufacturing initiatives, investigation of productivity improvements, time studies, establishment of routings, set-up production lines, order tooling for production requirements, manage the pilot process for new products, and represents the operations department in design reviews, design status, and project status meetings.&nbsp; Works with Engineering department to create and insure products made in production are reliable and meet specifications.&nbsp; Relies on extensive experience and judgment to plan and accomplish goals. Performs a variety of complex tasks.&nbsp; Works with the Engineering team to insure that everyone is working cohesively to achieve the desired result.&nbsp; Develops methods, software programs and tools required to test released product to insure that parts and finished goods meet specifications and are operating as designed.</p>
<ul>
<li>
&nbsp;Lead the Operations department in lean initiatives, Kaizen events, training on Lean concepts and continuous improvement. Review current production processes to identify improvements that can be made to improve overall efficiency and quality.&nbsp; Document all changes.</li>
<li>
Insure that all equipment in the production area is up and operational.&nbsp; Repair, send out for repair or arrange for support from engineering to correct any problems that are preventing production from producing product.</li>
<li>
Conduct pilot production runs to determine any bill of material issues, assembly issues, and tools required, development of work instructions.</li>
<li>
Develop and manage the test development processes, both hardware and software, used to validate components at suppliers and finished goods to insure that they meet specifications established by engineering.&nbsp;</li>
<li>
Insure that ISO-9000/ISO14001standards are current and are being followed and work instructions are written and kept up to date.</li>
<li>
Attend and participate in various meetings: design status, design reviews, project status, and departmental status meetings.</li>
<li>
Work with Engineering to give input on Design for Manufacturability (DFM), approval of component samples, understanding of product functions, and development of quality/ inspection criteria for finished product.</li>
<li>
Review audit results and make changes if required.&nbsp; This includes time studies, daily line audits and 6S audits.</li>
</ul>
<p>
<br />
<u><strong>Desired Skills &amp; Experience</strong></u></p>
<p>
Qualifications include but are not limited to:</p>
<ul>
<li>
Bachelor&rsquo;s degree in Electrical Engineering required.</li>
<li>
7-10 years working in manufacturing environment preferably on electronic products.</li>
<li>
2-5 years managing manufacturing engineering experience preferred.</li>
<li>
3-5 years&rsquo; experience in developing test software desired.</li>
<li>
Excellent understanding of ISO-9000 quality systems.</li>
<li>
3-5 years Lean Manufacturing experience.&nbsp; Lean certification preferable.</li>
</ul>
]]></description>
