			<description><![CDATA[<p>
<u><strong>Responsibilities Include:</strong></u></p>
<p>
The Quality Control (QC) Manager is responsible for the evaluation of finished goods and incoming components to insure that they meet specifications and will perform reliably in the field.&nbsp; Assist the engineers in development of quality control standards and methods of measurement.&nbsp; Work with the purchasing department in assessing vendor capabilities and supplier&rsquo;s quality system.&nbsp; Review Corrective Action Notifications (CANs) and issue to suppliers.&nbsp; Work with suppliers on their corrective actions to insure compliance to specifications.&nbsp; Conduct periodic supplier quality audits.&nbsp; Measure operational quality and report via published metrics as well as improvements that are needed.&nbsp; Manage the Vendor Quality Engineer (VQE) in the China office to insure that products received from China meet specifications before they are shipped to the US.</p>
<ul>
<li>
Manage the QC inspectors to insure that Midtronics quality standards are being met or exceeded.</li>
<li>
Manage the VQE in the China office to insure that products being shipped to the US meet specifications prior to shipment and any quality issued are reviewed with the supplier to determine root cause and corrective action.</li>
<li>
Review current inbound quality checklists to ensure that key aspects of the part are being measured.&nbsp; Do not change the engineering specific criteria, but you may add additional measures to insure quality.</li>
<li>
Set-up inspection area with appropriate measuring tools.&nbsp; Insure that inspection is always up-to-date with calibration certifications.&nbsp; Work with engineering and manufacturing engineering to create tools/fixtures/jigs to assist in the inspection processes.</li>
<li>
nsure that the in-process manufacturing quality standards are being met and that work instructions are being followed.</li>
<li>
Develop quality reporting metrics and report on results and processes put in place to remedy non-conformances.</li>
<li>
Visit suppliers and conduct quality audits of their processes and quality systems, review corrective actions to determine root cause of errors and that corrective action is effective.&nbsp;</li>
<li>
Work with purchasing and engineering when evaluating potential suppliers to determine if their quality systems and processes are capable of producing good quality parts.</li>
<li>
Work with the Division&rsquo;s quality representatives to comply with and enhance Midtronics&rsquo; Quality Management System (QMS).</li>
</ul>
<p>
<u><strong>Qualifications include but are not limited to:</strong></u></p>
<ul>
<li>
Bachelor&rsquo;s degree in Engineering or Quality required.</li>
<li>
7-10 years working in quality control department preferably on electronic products.</li>
<li>
2-5 years management experience preferred.</li>
<li>
Excellent understanding of ISO-9000 quality systems.</li>
<li>
Familiar with concepts, procedures and practices within the quality field.</li>
<li>
Experience with inspection methods and tools.</li>
<li>
Familiar with a variety of quality tools e.g. Six Sigma, TQM, PPAP, etc.</li>
<li>
American Society for Quality Certification (ASQ) a plus.</li>
</ul>
]]></description>
